The as-prepared system was used to detect UA in real samples including human serum and saliva samples. It was found that the recoveries% are in the range of 96.9–104.9% with RSD% not >2.8%, suggesting the reliability of the proposed system for the detection of UA (Table 2
                        ). In addition, the results were compared with commercial UA kits. It was found that there is no significant difference between them, confirming the accuracy of the system for UA detection. In addition, the student's t-test (paired t-test, t0.05) was used to compare the results obtained by the present method and commercial UA kits (Table 2). The results showed that there is no significant difference between two methods (texp.<ttable) (see Scheme 1
                        ).
